<div id="review_4049354876" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4049354876" />
    <a title="Tanvika" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/31284088-tanvika"><img alt="Tanvika" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1549347854p2/31284088.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4049354876?book_show_action=true">Jun 09, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tanvika" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tanvika" href="/user/show/31284088-tanvika">Tanvika</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4049354876" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7297327834476117834">The white man gaze loomed heavily in this book. obsession with poverty in Latin American countries. I couldn&apos;t connect with the writer&apos;s sense of humour. it does get condescending at times. Enjoyed the keen observation of the landscape and the socio-economic analysis of the region (colonialism, capitalist exploitation, hypernationalism etc). loved the chapter on Buenos aires and the literature loving interaction with Borges. satisfying conclusion in the nowhere land of Patagonia. </span>
  <span id="freeText7297327834476117834" style="display:none">The white man gaze loomed heavily in this book. obsession with poverty in Latin American countries. I couldn't connect with the writer's sense of humour. it does get condescending at times. Enjoyed the keen observation of the landscape and the socio-economic analysis of the region (colonialism, capitalist exploitation, hypernationalism etc). loved the chapter on Buenos aires and the literature loving interaction with Borges. satisfying conclusion in the nowhere land of Patagonia. </span>
